and 403 http status codes, and returns 200 ok for static error pages, a source of confusion for some admins.  on the other hand, the new server.error-handler, when set, will intercept all http status error codes >= 400.  server.error-handler takes precedence over server.error-handler-404 when both are set.  note: a major difference between server.error-handler and the now-deprecated server.error-handler-404 is that the values of the non-standard cgi environment variables request_uri and redirect_uri have been swapped.  since redirect_status is the original http status code, redirect_uri is now the original request, and request_uri is the current request (e.g. the uri/url to the error handler). the prior behavior -- which reversed request_uri and redirect_uri values from those described above -- is preserved for server.error-handler-404.  additionally, redirect_status is now available to mod_magnet, which continues to have access to request.uri and request.orig_uri.  see further discussion at https://redmine.lighttpd.net/issues/2702 and https://redmine.lighttpd.net/issues/1828  github: closes #36','configfile.c','1146','246','8','2','true','false','false','2016-04-25 01:01:08-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.30','bed63b79625cf98f41317b62519fa8abb7a82c1e','Glenn Strauss','[core] support ipv6 in $http[\"remote-ip\"] cidr cond match (fixes #2706)  x-ref:   \"matching ipv6 addresses with $http[\"remoteip\"]\"   https://redmine.lighttpd.net/issues/2706  github: closes #52','configfile-glue.c','512','158','99','52','true','true','false','2016-04-25 01:52:12-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.30','bed63b79625cf98f41317b62519fa8abb7a82c1e','Glenn Strauss','[core] support ipv6 in $http[\"remote-ip\"] cidr cond match (fixes #2706)  x-ref:   \"matching ipv6 addresses with $http[\"remoteip\"]\"   https://redmine.lighttpd.net/issues/2706  github: closes #52','configfile-glue.c','512','158','99','52','true','true','false','2016-04-25 01:52:12-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.30','bed63b79625cf98f41317b6251